label: King John's Jewels
Summary: King John allegedly lost royal regalia and gold in the treacherous marshes of The Wash in 1216. Despite centuries of searching
column6: no confirmed trace of the treasure has ever been uncovered.

label: Spainish Gold in Tobermory Bay
Summary: Some people believe the 'San Juan de Sicilia' which sank in the bay after a gunpowder incident - was a treasure galleon laden with gold.

label: Dunmail Raise Crown - Lake District
column7: King Dunmail crown is said to have been hurled into Grisedale Tarn to keep it from foes.
